ipsecMIB.name: ipsecMIB
ipsecMIB.contactinfo: Tim Jenkins TimeStep Corporation 362 Terry Fox Drive Kanata, ON K0A 2H0 Canada 613-599-3610 tjenkins@timestep.com
ipsecMIB.description: The MIB module to describe generic IPSec objects, and entity level IPSec objects and events.

ipsecProtSuiteTable.name: ipsecProtSuiteTable
ipsecProtSuiteTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on IPSec protection suites.

ipsecProtSuiteEntry.name: ipsecProtSuiteEntry
ipsecProtSuiteEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular IPSec protection suite.

ipsecProtSuiteIndex.name: ipsecProtSuiteIndex
ipsecProtSuiteIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each IPSec protection suite. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1.

ipsecProtSuiteLocalAddress.name: ipsecProtSuiteLocalAddress
ipsecProtSuiteLocalAddress.description: The local IP address used by the protection suite. The size of this object is 4 if the address is an IPv4 address, or 16 if the address is an IPv6 address.

ipsecProtSuiteRemoteAddress.name: ipsecProtSuiteRemoteAddress
ipsecProtSuiteRemoteAddress.description: The peer IP address used by the protection suite. The size of this object is 4 if the address is an IPv4 address, or 16 if the address is an IPv6 address.

ipsecProtSuiteInboundEspSpi.name: ipsecProtSuiteInboundEspSpi
ipsecProtSuiteInboundEspSpi.description: The value of the SPI for the inbound protection suite that provides the ESP security service, or zero if ESP is not used.

ipsecProtSuiteOutboundEspSpi.name: ipsecProtSuiteOutboundEspSpi
ipsecProtSuiteOutboundEspSpi.description: The value of the SPI for the outbound protection suite that provides the ESP security service, or zero if ESP is not used.

ipsecProtSuiteInboundAhSpi.name: ipsecProtSuiteInboundAhSpi
ipsecProtSuiteInboundAhSpi.description: The value of the SPI for the inbound protection suite that provides the AH security service, or zero if AH is not used.

ipsecProtSuiteOutboundAhSpi.name: ipsecProtSuiteOutboundAhSpi
ipsecProtSuiteOutboundAhSpi.description: The value of the SPI for the outbound protection suite that provides the AH security service, or zero if AH is not used.

ipsecProtSuiteInboundCompCpi.name: ipsecProtSuiteInboundCompCpi
ipsecProtSuiteInboundCompCpi.description: The value of the CPI for the inbound protection suite that provides IP compression, or zero if IPCOMP is not used.

ipsecProtSuiteOutboundCompCpi.name: ipsecProtSuiteOutboundCompCpi
ipsecProtSuiteOutboundCompCpi.description: The value of the CPI for the outbound protection suite that provides IP compression, or zero if IPCOMP is not used.

ipsecProtSuiteLocalId.name: ipsecProtSuiteLocalId
ipsecProtSuiteLocalId.description: The local identifier of the protection suite, or 0 if unknown or if the protection suite uses transport mode encapsulation. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchange during phase 2 negotiations.

ipsecProtSuiteLocalIdType.name: ipsecProtSuiteLocalIdType
ipsecProtSuiteLocalIdType.description: The type of identifier presented by 'ipsecTunnelLocalId', or 0 if unknown or if the protection suite uses transport mode encapsulation. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchange during phase 2 negotiations.

ipsecProtSuiteRemoteId.name: ipsecProtSuiteRemoteId
ipsecProtSuiteRemoteId.description: The remote identifier of the protection suite, or 0 if unknown or if the protection suite uses transport mode encapsulation. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchange during phase 2 negotiations.

ipsecProtSuiteRemoteIdType.name: ipsecProtSuiteRemoteIdType
ipsecProtSuiteRemoteIdType.description: The type of identifier presented by 'ipsecTunnelRemoteId', or 0 if unknown or if the protection suite uses transport mode encapsulation. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchange during phase 2 negotiations.

ipsecProtSuiteProtocol.name: ipsecProtSuiteProtocol
ipsecProtSuiteProtocol.description: The IP protocol number that this protection suite carries, or 0 if it carries any protocol.

ipsecProtSuiteLocalPort.name: ipsecProtSuiteLocalPort
ipsecProtSuiteLocalPort.description: The local UDP or TCP port number that this protection suite carries, or 0 if it carries any port number.

ipsecProtSuiteRemotePort.name: ipsecProtSuiteRemotePort
ipsecProtSuiteRemotePort.description: The remote UDP or TCP port number that this protection suite carries, or 0 if it carries any port number.

ipsecProtSuiteDifHelGroupDesc.name: ipsecProtSuiteDifHelGroupDesc
ipsecProtSuiteDifHelGroupDesc.description: A unique value representing the Diffie-Hellman group description used to set up this protection suite, or 0 if the description is unknown. Specific values are used as described in the ISAKMP Class Values of Group Description from Appendix A of [IKE].

ipsecProtSuiteDifHelGroupType.name: ipsecProtSuiteDifHelGroupType
ipsecProtSuiteDifHelGroupType.description: A unique value representing the Diffie-Hellman group type used to set up this protection suite, or 0 if the type is unknown. Specific values are used as described in the ISAKMP Class Values of Group Type from Appendix A of [IKE].

ipsecProtSuitePFS.name: ipsecProtSuitePFS
ipsecProtSuitePFS.description: 'true' if the protection suite was created using perfect forward secrect.

ipsecProtSuiteEncapsulation.name: ipsecProtSuiteEncapsulation
ipsecProtSuiteEncapsulation.description: The type of encapsulation used by this protection suite.

ipsecProtSuiteEspEncAlg.name: ipsecProtSuiteEspEncAlg
ipsecProtSuiteEspEncAlg.description: A unique value representing the encryption algorithm applied to traffic carried by this protection suite if it uses ESP or 0 if there is no encryption applied by ESP or if ESP is not used. Specific values are taken from section 4.4.4 of [IPDOI].

ipsecProtSuiteEspEncKeyLength.name: ipsecProtSuiteEspEncKeyLength
ipsecProtSuiteEspEncKeyLength.description: The length of the encryption key in bits used for the algorithm specified in the 'ipsecTunnelEspEncAlg' object, or 0 if the key length is implicit in the specified algorithm or there is no encryption specified.

ipsecProtSuiteEspAuthAlg.name: ipsecProtSuiteEspAuthAlg
ipsecProtSuiteEspAuthAlg.description: A unique value representing the hash algorithm applied to traffic carried by this protection suite if it uses ESP or 0 if there is no authentication applied by ESP or if ESP is not used. Specific values are taken from the Authentication Algorithm attribute values of Section 4.5 of [IPDOI].

ipsecProtSuiteAhAuthAlg.name: ipsecProtSuiteAhAuthAlg
ipsecProtSuiteAhAuthAlg.description: A unique value representing the hash algorithm applied to traffic carried by this protection suite if it uses AH or 0 if AH is not used. Specific values are taken from Section 4.4.3 of [IPDOI].

ipsecProtSuiteCompAlg.name: ipsecProtSuiteCompAlg
ipsecProtSuiteCompAlg.description: A unique value representing the compression algorithm applied to traffic carried by this protection suite if it uses IPCOMP. Specific values are taken from Section 4.4.5 of [IPDOI].

ipsecProtSuiteCreationTime.name: ipsecProtSuiteCreationTime
ipsecProtSuiteCreationTime.description: The date and time that the current protection suite was set up.

ipsecProtSuiteTimeLimit.name: ipsecProtSuiteTimeLimit
ipsecProtSuiteTimeLimit.description: The maximum lifetime in seconds of the protection suite, or 0 if there is no time constraint on its expiration.

ipsecProtSuiteTrafficLimit.name: ipsecProtSuiteTrafficLimit
ipsecProtSuiteTrafficLimit.description: The maximum traffic in 1024-byte blocks that the protection suite is allowed to support, or 0 if there is no traffic constraint on its expiration.

ipsecProtSuiteInTrafficCount.name: ipsecProtSuiteInTrafficCount
ipsecProtSuiteInTrafficCount.description: The amount of inbound traffic accumulated that counts against the protection suite's expiration by traffic limitation, measured in 1024-byte blocks. This value may be 0 if the protection suite does not expire based on traffic. In the case of multiple SAs within a protection suite, this value is the maximum of any traffic accumulation values applied to any of the individual SAs within the protection suite.

ipsecProtSuiteOutTrafficCount.name: ipsecProtSuiteOutTrafficCount
ipsecProtSuiteOutTrafficCount.description: The amount of outbound traffic accumulated that counts against the protection suite's expiration by traffic limitation, measured in 1024-byte blocks. This value may be 0 if the protection suite does not expire based on traffic. In the case of multiple SAs within a protection suite, this value is the maximum of any traffic accumulation values applied to any of the individual SAs within the protection suite.

ipsecProtSuiteInboundTraffic.name: ipsecProtSuiteInboundTraffic
ipsecProtSuiteInboundTraffic.description: The amount of user level traffic measured in bytes handled by the protection suite in the inbound direction. This is not necessarily the same as the amount of traffic applied against the traffic expiration limit.

ipsecProtSuiteOutboundTraffic.name: ipsecProtSuiteOutboundTraffic
ipsecProtSuiteOutboundTraffic.description: The amount of user level traffic measured in bytes handled by the protection suite in the outbound direction. This is not necessarily the same as the amount of traffic applied against the traffic expiration limit.

ipsecProtSuiteInboundPackets.name: ipsecProtSuiteInboundPackets
ipsecProtSuiteInboundPackets.description: The number of packets handled by the protection suite in the inbound direction.

ipsecProtSuiteOutboundPackets.name: ipsecProtSuiteOutboundPackets
ipsecProtSuiteOutboundPackets.description: The number of packets handled by the protection suite in the outbound direction.

ipsecProtSuiteDecryptErrors.name: ipsecProtSuiteDecryptErrors
ipsecProtSuiteDecryptErrors.description: The number of inbound packets discarded by the protection suite due to decryption errors.

ipsecProtSuiteAuthErrors.name: ipsecProtSuiteAuthErrors
ipsecProtSuiteAuthErrors.description: The number of inbound packets discarded by the protection suite due to authentication errors. This includes hash failures in both ESP and AH.

ipsecProtSuiteReplayErrors.name: ipsecProtSuiteReplayErrors
ipsecProtSuiteReplayErrors.description: The number of inbound packets discarded by the protection suite due to replay errors. This includes replay failures both ESP and AH.

ipsecProtSuitePolicyErrors.name: ipsecProtSuitePolicyErrors
ipsecProtSuitePolicyErrors.description: The number of inbound packets discarded by the protection suite due to policy errors.

ipsecProtSuiteOtherReceiveErrors.name: ipsecProtSuiteOtherReceiveErrors
ipsecProtSuiteOtherReceiveErrors.description: The number of inbound packets discarded by the protection suite due to errors other than decryption, authentication or replay errors. This may include decompression errors or errors due to a lack of receive buffers.

ipsecProtSuiteSendErrors.name: ipsecProtSuiteSendErrors
ipsecProtSuiteSendErrors.description: The number of outbound packets discarded by the protection suite due to any error. This may include compression errors or errors due to a lack of transmit buffers.

ipsecIkeSaTable.name: ipsecIkeSaTable
ipsecIkeSaTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on IPSec's IKE SAs.

ipsecIkeSaEntry.name: ipsecIkeSaEntry
ipsecIkeSaEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular IKE SA.

ipsecIkeSaIndex.name: ipsecIkeSaIndex
ipsecIkeSaIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each phase 1 SA. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each entry must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ipsecIkeSaInitiatorCookie.name: ipsecIkeSaInitiatorCookie
ipsecIkeSaInitiatorCookie.description: The value of the cookie used by the initiator for the phase 1 SA.

ipsecIkeSaResponderCookie.name: ipsecIkeSaResponderCookie
ipsecIkeSaResponderCookie.description: The value of the cookie used by the responder for the phase 1 SA.

ipsecIkeSaLocalIpAddress.name: ipsecIkeSaLocalIpAddress
ipsecIkeSaLocalIpAddress.description: The local IP address used to negotiated the SA. The size of the object is 4 if the address is an IPv4 address and 16 if an IPv6 address.

ipsecIkeSaLocalPortNumber.name: ipsecIkeSaLocalPortNumber
ipsecIkeSaLocalPortNumber.description: The local UDP port number that this SA was negotiated with.

ipsecIkeSaLocalIdType.name: ipsecIkeSaLocalIdType
ipsecIkeSaLocalIdType.description: The type of ID used by the local end of this SA. Specific values are used as described in Section 4.6.2.1 of [IPDOI].

ipsecIkeSaLocalId.name: ipsecIkeSaLocalId
ipsecIkeSaLocalId.description: The ID of the local host that negotiated this SA. The length may require truncation under some conditions.

ipsecIkeSaPeerIpAddress.name: ipsecIkeSaPeerIpAddress
ipsecIkeSaPeerIpAddress.description: The IP address of the peer that this SA was negotiated with. The size of the object is 4 if the address is an IPv4 address and 16 if it is an IPv6 address.

ipsecIkeSaPeerPortNumber.name: ipsecIkeSaPeerPortNumber
ipsecIkeSaPeerPortNumber.description: The UDP port number of the peer that this SA was negotiated with.

ipsecIkeSaAuthMethod.name: ipsecIkeSaAuthMethod
ipsecIkeSaAuthMethod.description: The authentication method used to authenticate the peer. Note that this does not include the specific method of authentication if extended authenticated is used. Specific values are used as described in the ISAKMP Class Values of Authentication Method from Appendix A of [IKE].

ipsecIkeSaPeerIdType.name: ipsecIkeSaPeerIdType
ipsecIkeSaPeerIdType.description: The type of ID used by the peer. Specific values are used as described in Section 4.6.2.1 of [IPDOI].

ipsecIkeSaPeerId.name: ipsecIkeSaPeerId
ipsecIkeSaPeerId.description: The ID of the peer this SA was negotiated with. The length may require truncation under some conditions.

ipsecIkeSaPeerCertSerialNum.name: ipsecIkeSaPeerCertSerialNum
ipsecIkeSaPeerCertSerialNum.description: The serial number of the certificate of the peer this SA was negotiated with. This object has no meaning if a certificate was not used in authenticating the peer.

ipsecIkeSaPeerCertIssuer.name: ipsecIkeSaPeerCertIssuer
ipsecIkeSaPeerCertIssuer.description: The issuer of the certificate of the peer this SA was negotiated with. This object has no meaning if a certificate was not used in authenticating the peer.

ipsecIkeSaEncAlg.name: ipsecIkeSaEncAlg
ipsecIkeSaEncAlg.description: A unique value representing the encryption algorithm applied to traffic carried by this SA. Specific values are used as described in the ISAKMP Class Values of Encryption Algorithms from Appendix A of [IKE].

ipsecIkeSaEncKeyLength.name: ipsecIkeSaEncKeyLength
ipsecIkeSaEncKeyLength.description: The length of the encryption key in bits used for algorithm specified in the ipsecIkeSaEncAlg object or 0 if the key length is implicit in the specified algorithm.

ipsecIkeSaHashAlg.name: ipsecIkeSaHashAlg
ipsecIkeSaHashAlg.description: A unique value representing the hash algorithm applied to traffic carried by this SA. Specific values are used as described in the ISAKMP Class Values of Hash Algorithms from Appendix A of [IKE].

ipsecIkeSaDifHelGroupDesc.name: ipsecIkeSaDifHelGroupDesc
ipsecIkeSaDifHelGroupDesc.description: A unique value representing the Diffie-Hellman group description used or 0 if the group is unknown. Specific values are used as described in the ISAKMP Class Values of Group Description from Appendix A of [IKE].

ipsecIkeSaDifHelGroupType.name: ipsecIkeSaDifHelGroupType
ipsecIkeSaDifHelGroupType.description: A unique value representing the Diffie-Hellman group type used or 0 if the group is unknown. Specific values are used as described in the ISAKMP Class Values of Group Type from Appendix A of [IKE].

ipsecIkeSaDifHelFieldSize.name: ipsecIkeSaDifHelFieldSize
ipsecIkeSaDifHelFieldSize.description: The field size, in bits, of the Diffie-Hellman group used to generate the key-pair, or 0 if unknown.

ipsecIkeSaPRF.name: ipsecIkeSaPRF
ipsecIkeSaPRF.description: The pseudo-random functions used, or 0 if not used or if unknown. Specific values are used as described in the ISAKMP Class Values of PRF from Appendix A of [IKE] (which specifies none at the present time).

ipsecIkeSaPFS.name: ipsecIkeSaPFS
ipsecIkeSaPFS.description: A value that indicates that perfect forward secrecy is used for all IPSec SAs created by this IKE SA.

ipsecIkeSaTimeStart.name: ipsecIkeSaTimeStart
ipsecIkeSaTimeStart.description: The date and time that the SA was set up.

ipsecIkeSaTimeLimit.name: ipsecIkeSaTimeLimit
ipsecIkeSaTimeLimit.description: The maximum lifetime in seconds of the SA, or 0 if there is no time constraint on its expiration.

ipsecIkeSaTrafficLimit.name: ipsecIkeSaTrafficLimit
ipsecIkeSaTrafficLimit.description: The maximum traffic in 1024-byte blocks that the SA is allowed to carry, or 0 if there is no traffic constraint on its expiration.

ipsecIkeSaInboundTraffic.name: ipsecIkeSaInboundTraffic
ipsecIkeSaInboundTraffic.description: The amount traffic measured in bytes handled in the SA in the inbound direction.

ipsecIkeSaOutboundTraffic.name: ipsecIkeSaOutboundTraffic
ipsecIkeSaOutboundTraffic.description: The amount traffic measured in bytes handled in the SA in the outbound direction.

ipsecIkeSaInboundPackets.name: ipsecIkeSaInboundPackets
ipsecIkeSaInboundPackets.description: The number of packets handled in the SA in the inbound direction.

ipsecIkeSaOutboundPackets.name: ipsecIkeSaOutboundPackets
ipsecIkeSaOutboundPackets.description: The number of packets handled in the SA in the outbound direction.

ipsecIkeProtSuitesCreated.name: ipsecIkeProtSuitesCreated
ipsecIkeProtSuitesCreated.description: The total number of phase 2 protection suites created by the SA.

ipsecIkeProtSuitesDeleted.name: ipsecIkeProtSuitesDeleted
ipsecIkeProtSuitesDeleted.description: The total number of phase 2 protection suites deleted by the SA.

ipsecIkeSaDecryptErrors.name: ipsecIkeSaDecryptErrors
ipsecIkeSaDecryptErrors.description: The number of inbound packets discarded by the phase1 SA due to decryption errors.

ipsecIkeSaAuthErrors.name: ipsecIkeSaAuthErrors
ipsecIkeSaAuthErrors.description: The number of inbound packets discarded by the phase 1 SA due to authentication errors.

ipsecIkeSaOtherReceiveErrors.name: ipsecIkeSaOtherReceiveErrors
ipsecIkeSaOtherReceiveErrors.description: The number of inbound packets discarded by the phase 1 SA due to errors other than decryption or authentication errors. This may include errors due to a lack of receive buffers.

ipsecIkeSaSendErrors.name: ipsecIkeSaSendErrors
ipsecIkeSaSendErrors.description: The number of outbound packets discarded by the phase 1 SA due to any error. This may include errors due to a lack of transmit buffers.

ipsecIpsecTotalProtSuites.name: ipsecIpsecTotalProtSuites
ipsecIpsecTotalProtSuites.description: The total number of phase 2 protection suites established by the entity since boot time.

ipsecIpsecNegFailures.name: ipsecIpsecNegFailures
ipsecIpsecNegFailures.description: The total number of phase 2 protection suite negotiations that failed that occurred in the entity since boot time.

ipsecIpsecTotalInboundPackets.name: ipsecIpsecTotalInboundPackets
ipsecIpsecTotalInboundPackets.description: The total number of inbound packets carried on IPSec protection suites since boot time.

ipsecIpsecTotalTransOutboundPackets.name: ipsecIpsecTotalTransOutboundPackets
ipsecIpsecTotalTransOutboundPackets.description: The total number of outbound packets carried on IPSec protection suites since boot time.

ipsecIpsecTotalTransInboundTraffic.name: ipsecIpsecTotalTransInboundTraffic
ipsecIpsecTotalTransInboundTraffic.description: The total amount of inbound traffic carried on IPSec protection suites since boot time, measured in 1024-octet blocks.

ipsecIpsecTotalTransOutboundTraffic.name: ipsecIpsecTotalTransOutboundTraffic
ipsecIpsecTotalTransOutboundTraffic.description: The total amount of outbound traffic carried on IPSec protection suites since boot time, measured in 1024-octet blocks.

ipsecIpsecDecryptionErrors.name: ipsecIpsecDecryptionErrors
ipsecIpsecDecryptionErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in the IPSec protection suites since boot time with decryption errors.

ipsecIpsecAuthenticationErrors.name: ipsecIpsecAuthenticationErrors
ipsecIpsecAuthenticationErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in the IPSec protection suites since boot time with authentication errors. This includes all packets in which the hash value is determined to be invalid.

ipsecIpsecReplayErrors.name: ipsecIpsecReplayErrors
ipsecIpsecReplayErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in the IPSec protection suites since boot time with replay errors.

ipsecIpsecPolicyErrors.name: ipsecIpsecPolicyErrors
ipsecIpsecPolicyErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in the IPSec protection suites since boot time and discarded due to policy errors. This includes packets that had selectors that were invalid for the SA or protection suite that carried them.

ipsecIpsecOtherReceiveErrors.name: ipsecIpsecOtherReceiveErrors
ipsecIpsecOtherReceiveErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in the IPSec protection suites since boot time and discarded due to errors not due to decryption, authentication, replay or policy.

ipsecIpsecSendErrors.name: ipsecIpsecSendErrors
ipsecIpsecSendErrors.description: The total number of packets to be sent by the entity in the IPSec protection suites since boot time and discarded due to errors.

ipsecUnknownSpiErrors.name: ipsecUnknownSpiErrors
ipsecUnknownSpiErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity since boot time with SPIs or CPIs that were not valid.

ipsecIkeTotalSAs.name: ipsecIkeTotalSAs
ipsecIkeTotalSAs.description: The total number of phase 1 SAs successfully established by the entity since boot time.

ipsecIkeNegFailures.name: ipsecIkeNegFailures
ipsecIkeNegFailures.description: The total number of phase 1 SA negotiations that failed that occurred in the entity since boot time.

ipsecIkeTotalInboundPackets.name: ipsecIkeTotalInboundPackets
ipsecIkeTotalInboundPackets.description: The total number of inbound packets carried on phase 1 SAs since boot time.

ipsecIkeTotalTransOutboundPackets.name: ipsecIkeTotalTransOutboundPackets
ipsecIkeTotalTransOutboundPackets.description: The total number of outbound packets carried on phase 1 SAs since boot time.

ipsecIkeTotalTransInboundTraffic.name: ipsecIkeTotalTransInboundTraffic
ipsecIkeTotalTransInboundTraffic.description: The total amount of inbound traffic carried on phase 1 SAs since boot time, measured in 1024-octet blocks.

ipsecIkeTotalTransOutboundTraffic.name: ipsecIkeTotalTransOutboundTraffic
ipsecIkeTotalTransOutboundTraffic.description: The total amount of outbound traffic carried on phase 1 SAs since boot time, measured in 1024-octet blocks.

ipsecIkeProtocolErrors.name: ipsecIkeProtocolErrors
ipsecIkeProtocolErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity since boot time with IKE protocol errors. This includes packets with invalid cookies, but does not include errors that are associated with specific IKE SAs.

ipsecIkeDecryptionErrors.name: ipsecIkeDecryptionErrors
ipsecIkeDecryptionErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in the IPSec protection suites since boot time with decryption errors.

ipsecIkeAuthenticationErrors.name: ipsecIkeAuthenticationErrors
ipsecIkeAuthenticationErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in the IPSec protection suites since boot time with authentication errors. This includes all packets in which the hash value is determined to be invalid.

ipsecIkeOtherReceiveErrors.name: ipsecIkeOtherReceiveErrors
ipsecIkeOtherReceiveErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in phase 1 SAs since boot time and discarded due to errors not due to decryption or authentication.

ipsecIkeSendErrors.name: ipsecIkeSendErrors
ipsecIkeSendErrors.description: The total number of packets to be sent by the entity in phase 1 SAs since boot time and discarded due to errors.

ipsecNotifyMessageTotalCount.name: ipsecNotifyMessageTotalCount
ipsecNotifyMessageTotalCount.description: The total number of all types of notify messages sent or received by the entity since boot time. It is the sum of all occurrences in the 'ipsecNotifyCountTable'.

ipsecNotifyCountTable.name: ipsecNotifyCountTable
ipsecNotifyCountTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on IPSec notify message counts. This table MAY be sparsely populated; that is, rows for which the count is 0 may be absent.

ipsecNotifyCountEntry.name: ipsecNotifyCountEntry
ipsecNotifyCountEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the total number of occurrences of a notify message.

ipsecNotifyMessage.name: ipsecNotifyMessage
ipsecNotifyMessage.description: The value representing a specific IPSec notify message, or 0 if unknown. Values are assigned from the set of notify message types as defined in Section 3.14.1 of [ISAKMP]. In addition, the value 0 may be used for this object when the object is used as a trap cause, and the cause is unknown.

ipsecNotifyMessageCount.name: ipsecNotifyMessageCount
ipsecNotifyMessageCount.description: The total number of times the specific notify message has been received or sent by the entity since system boot.

ipsecTrapIkeNegFailure.name: ipsecTrapIkeNegFailure
ipsecTrapIkeNegFailure.description: An attempt to negotiate a phase 1 SA failed.

ipsecTrapInvalidCookie.name: ipsecTrapInvalidCookie
ipsecTrapInvalidCookie.description: IKE packets with invalid cookies were detected from the specified peer. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per peer (within a reasonable time period, rather than sending one trap per packet.

ipsecTrapIpsecNegFailure.name: ipsecTrapIpsecNegFailure
ipsecTrapIpsecNegFailure.description: An attempt to negotiate a phase 2 protection suite within the specified IKE SA failed.

ipsecTrapIpsecAuthFailure.name: ipsecTrapIpsecAuthFailure
ipsecTrapIpsecAuthFailure.description: IPSec packets with invalid hashes were found in the specified protection suite. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per protection suite (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

ipsecTrapIpsecReplayFailure.name: ipsecTrapIpsecReplayFailure
ipsecTrapIpsecReplayFailure.description: IPSec packets with invalid sequence numbers were found in the specified protection suite. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per protection suite (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

ipsecTrapIpsecPolicyFailure.name: ipsecTrapIpsecPolicyFailure
ipsecTrapIpsecPolicyFailure.description: IPSec packets carrying packets with invalid selectors for the specified protection suite were found. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per protection suite (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

ipsecTrapInvalidSpi.name: ipsecTrapInvalidSpi
ipsecTrapInvalidSpi.description: ESP, AH or IPCOMP packets with unknown SPIs (or CPIs) were detected from the specified peer. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per peer (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.
